f=Engineering/dana/custom/data-modeling/SKILL.md · in=data-modeling dana's schema discipline: designing entities, relationships, keys, constraints WITHIN chosen store data correct construction database enforces what application trusted to. Whether relational (normalization, foreign keys, constraints), graph (nodes/edges/properties), vector (embedding schema metadata), goal same: make invalid states unrepresentable. · p=data bugs modeling failures: nullable column shouldn't be, missing foreign key let orphans accumulate, duplicated data drifted out sync. good model pushes correctness schema constraint database enforces can't forgotten application code, agent especially can't "forget" NULL way skip validation. · wu=Triggers: "design schema," "model data," "what tables/collections," "should normalized," "foreign keys," "how relate Y," any new entity relationship chosen store. · st:/ Protocol=`An entity/domain to model (in the store chosen by datastore-selection) \· -> Identify entities, their identity (keys), and relationships (cardinality, optionality) \· -> Push correctness into the schema: \· relational → normalize to remove redundancy \· FKs \· NOT NULL \· UNIQUE \· CHECK constraints \· graph → node/edge types \· required properties \· relationship direction/cardinality` · in=**Model identity first.** What uniquely identifies entity (natural surrogate key), what relationships (one-to-many, many-to-many, optional required)? Getting identity cardinality right modeling; rest follows. **Constraints over conventions.** rule database enforces (FK, NULL, UNIQUE, CHECK) beats rule application supposed follow especially agent-authored code, which skip validation cannot skip schema constraint. Make invalid states unrepresentable. **Normalize default; denormalize evidence.** Start normalized (no redundant data drift out sync). Denormalize measured read pattern demands (axiom/db-performance evidence), explicit sync story recorded, redundancy decision, accident. **Model store's paradigm.** Don't impose relational habits graph (relationships first-class edges, join tables) document store (embed reference core choice). paradigm chosen shape datastore-selection; model shape. **Vectors need source truth.** Embeddings derived data; model records what they're derived they're kept fresh (re-embed source change). vector store whose embeddings silently drift their source correctness bug. **Schema changes through migrations.** model change live store never applied directly it's migration-discipline script operator runs (Rail 3). Modeling design; applying migration. · of=`## Data Model: [domain] — [store/paradigm] \· Entities + keys: [entity \· identity \· key type] \· Relationships: [A —(cardinality)— B \· required?] \· Constraints (invalid states unrepresentable): [FK/NOT NULL/UNIQUE/CHECK \· graph edge rules \· vector schema] \· Normalization: [normalized / denormalized-with-reason + sync story]` · pr=**Model identity cardinality first** rest follows., **Constraints over conventions** enforces what agent code skip., **Invalid states unrepresentable** push correctness schema., **Normalize default, denormalize measured evidence** redundancy recorded decision, never accident., **Model store's paradigm** graphs aren't join tables; documents choose embed-vs-reference., **Derived data (vectors) names source** drift source correctness bug. · f=Requirements unclear/evolving model stable core constraints, leave genuinely uncertain areas flexible (nullable/optional) labeled, tighten requirements firm; don't over-constrain speculation., Performance pressure denormalize early require measured read pattern first (db-performance/axiom); premature denormalization redundancy drifts., Legacy schema can't take new constraints cleanly add constraints migration incrementally (validate-then-enforce), never big-bang locks table. · b:with Other Skills=**datastore-selection** (sibling) chose store; designs schema within it., **migration-discipline** (sibling) applies schema change Rail operator-run., **db-performance** (sibling) supplies measured read patterns justify denormalization indexes model needs., **axiom**: storage-structure complexity informs graph/index modeling., **raj**: API's data contracts reflect model; mismatch integration bug., **aegis/cypher**: vector/embedding weaknesses (OWASP LLM L08) modeling-adjacent attack surface RAG stores.